<plot>This one-hour documentary explores the contentious debate over gun control, as seen through the eyes of two mothers on opposite sides of the issue. Frances Davis from Brooklyn lost all three of her sons to gun violence and is a fierce advocate of gun control. Maria Heil rural Pennsylvanian mother of four, serves as spokeswoman for the Second Amendment Sisters, a group formed in response to the Million Mom March in 2000.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?225037</url></doc>
